            , a Jew. I got a constable, and secured the prisoner, and asked him how he came by them; he said they were his uncle's property; there were three tea spoons and a pair of tongs (produced in court)</p>
               <p>Adlington. These are my property, they were in the tea-chest when it was taken away.</p>
               <p>Marks. The prisoner owned he went into a cook's-shop in Shoe-lane, and took them away; I went to the prosecutor's house, his wife told me she had lost a tea-chest and these things the night before.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence</p>
               <p>I was very much in liquor, but do not remember any thing of it.</p>
